dblp.social.preparser
Class XMLPartsInfo

java.lang.Object
  dblp.social.preparser.XMLPartsInfo

public class XMLPartsInfo
extends java.lang.Object

This class defines a structure used to memorize the pre-parse execution output in an xml file. It keeps track of: the source xml file and all the generated _part files. For each _part file its length and the number of inserted checkpoints is stored. The fields last-checkpoint and last-offset are also initialized.

Author:
Staffiero

appendPartFile

public void appendPartFile(java.lang.String filename,
                           long checkpoints,
                           long length)
Adds informations of a generated _part file to the current list. It is supposed to be called after the _part file has been closed, in order to receive the right informations about its lenght and number of checkpoints

Parameters:
filename: - the _part file name
checkpoints: - the number of checkpoints inserted into the _part file
length: - the _part file length

savePartFileInfo

public java.lang.String savePartFileInfo()
                                  throws FileExistsException,
                                         java.io.IOException
Saves the gathered informations to an xml file. This xml file should be used to know exactly which _part files are supposed to be sent to the parser, given a source xml file.

Throws:
FileExistsException
java.io.IOException
